About us

Who we are

Our Mission

Restoration of Life Transitional Homes is a faith‑based nonprofit in Anna, Texas. We provide short‑term housing and wrap‑around care for individuals and families working toward stability, sobriety, and self‑sufficiency.

Our team offers coaching, goal setting, and connections to jobs, benefits, and long‑term housing resources—because a safe place is only the beginning.

Who we serve

  • Individuals and parents with children seeking stable housing
  • Neighbors exiting crisis, shelters, or unsafe situations
  • Those committed to a structured, supportive environment

We welcome everyone with dignity—no one walks alone.

How to apply

Contact our team

Call (901) 538‑1330 or email Mentorship101@outlook.com to check availability and fit.

Meet & Plan

We’ll discuss goals, expectations, and next steps to build a plan toward stability.

Move‑in

Bring basic essentials. We’ll provide a safe space, structure, and support while you work your plan.

Grow Forward

With mentorship and resources, take the next step—employment, benefits, and long‑term housing.
